<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-15T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="792" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.51/383a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul in Chargé of the Legation in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-15T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                        1919—10 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department desires that if possible during an informal conversation with
                            President Bográn you discreetly discuss with him the desirability of
                            having a report prepared of the Honduran financial system with a view to
                            eventually placing Honduran finances on a satisfactory basis. It is
                            suggested that if possible Bográn request the Department for the
                            services of an expert to make the report referred to.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>